Description:
Secure Villa Unit
Excellent opportunity to invest, downsize or buy first home. Villa unit in a group of only four. Comprising entry, 2 Bedrooms with BIRS, Bathroom with bath & shower, Separate toilet. Combined kitchen/dining, lounge room, separate laundry and lock up single garage.
Conveniently located within 550m walking distance to Ormond train station & shops, close to Monash University and Kilvington Grammar.
For further information or to request a floor plan, please contact Malvern Real Estate on 9822 1000.

Description:
Design Flair With A Family Focus
Classically Californian first impressions are complemented by contemporary spaces of such style and scale that you stop and stare - loving the light and the luxury, enjoying the indoor-outdoor impact, imagining your family in such exceptional surroundings. Living/dining areas featuring polished concrete floors and an entertainer's kitchen with a butler's pantry illustrate the quality of a design that delivers a state-of-the-art cinema and three distinct alfresco zones including a decked domain with integrated spa, TV, barbeque bench and a sauna. The flexibility of four bedrooms and two flawless bathrooms, including a sublime main suite with its own deck access, confirms the family focus, complemented by a versatile, inviting central study/retreat and two additional powder rooms. Secure parking for two cars. A family home of unforgettable style, zoned to McKinnon Secondary College, close to local shopping and the station. Superb! Land size: 650sqm approx.
PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT ALL INSPECTIONS
PLEASE NOTE: Open for Inspection Times and Property Availability is subject to change or cancellation without notice. Melway Ref 68D9

Description:
Unrivalled Entertainer in the McKinnon Zones Best Location!
Impeccably crafted, paying the utmost attention to luxury and detail, this 5-bedroom, 5-bathroom, 5 living zone home sets the standard for high end, high tech living all within a highly sought McKinnon zone location.
A carefully considered floorplan places 3 bedrooms upstairs (each with their own ensuite and walk in robes) a choice of lounge on each level (including a first floor retreat and a dedicated home theatre), a fitted home office or private study alcove and luxe designer bathrooms with full height tiling (vast dual vanity ensuite).
Exquisitely detailed with polished bamboo flooring and Caesar stone benchtops throughout, this palatial home extends far beyond the grand entrance hall to a gas log fire warmed open plan area that blends informal lounge and dining areas with a streamlined Miele appliance kitchen featuring double ovens, a fully integrated bar with wine cabinetry and a separate butler's pantry.
Then find your piece of paradise in the family backyard where bi-fold doors open wide to an unrivalled resort style setting showcasing spotted gum decking for the covered al fresco, a striking feature fireplace and a built in barbeque.
But entertaining doesn't end there.... With lawn space for the kids, a Bali hut and bluestone pavers for the solar heated, salt water pool and a versatile living retreat (adaptable as a workshop or studio) comprising its own full bathroom and kitchenette.
Appointed with the very latest in modern technology, this smart home works with keyless video entry, zoned refrigerated air-con, ducted heating, LED lighting, a fitted projector for the home theatre & elite practicalities in a formal lounge/5th bedroom, quality storage, off street parking beyond auto gates, a separate carport and a rear double lock up garage.
Even the location is elite - with Joyce park across the road, the back gates to the College around the corner, McKinnon Primary within a stroll and a choice of McKinnon and North Roads shopping strip and station in close proximity. Land size - 744sqm approx. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Prized McKinnon Zone Home on a Gorgeous Garden Corner
Stretching wide on a prized cul-de-sac corner, this timeless 3-bedroom home has wide appeal for young families, renovators and developers alike within a prized McKinnon zone/Brighton East location.
Amidst a perfectly private garden sanctuary, a generous dual zone design places formal living at the front, informal lounge and dining at the rear, 2 robe fitted bedrooms in-between and a 3rd bedroom/retreat beside a separate WC.
Classically appointed with a retro style bathroom and a huge kitchen with meals, the elegant cream brick design even extends outdoors to an entertaining alfresco area (built in barbeque) against a beautiful backdrop of slate stone pavers and gorgeous garden walls.
Featuring polished floorboards and timber venetian blinds, there's panel hydronic heating and air conditioning for comfort, alarm for security, fresh paint for presentation and a double lock up garage with built in storage and side access from Minette Court.
Enjoy as is, transform this home and meet the market for great family living with a high quality renovation or look to this prime corner site on 578sqm approx as the location for all new prestige living with a brand new home or two (subject to council approval).
With major road access to the city and surf, parks and prestigious schools in close proximity, bayside amenities within minutes and a choice of zone 1/2 public transport in reach, this is lifestyle excellence in a lifetime location. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Price Reduced! All Offers Considered!
Super Spacious with Fabulous Courtyard Appeal
Set yourself up in this stylish ground floor 2 bedroom security apartment and love the sense of open private space with its generous wrap around garden courtyard. Open and airy, this dynamic retreat features an entry hall, open plan living & dining opening onto a casual courtyard with raised garden beds under a shady tree, designer stone kitchen with Italian stainless steel appliances, 2 double bedrooms (BIRs/WIR), sleek semi ensuite bathroom and a European laundry. The serene courtyard wraps around the apartment to a sun drenched north-east facing entertaining courtyard. With the comfort of R/C air conditioning, panel heating and security intercom, this lifestyle pad is complete with security basement parking and a storage cage. In this quiet street, a heartbeat to North Road shops, cafes, restaurants, the Monash Uni bus, the new Ormond station, schools and parkland.
** Please note: Bedrooms have being digitally furnished for advertising purposes.

Description:
Charming Corner Californian With Compelling Options In The Zone
Perfectly picturesque from period profile to contemporary interior & beyond to a superb entertainers' garden, this outstanding 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom Californian Bungalow is perfect for today with options for tomorrow. Resting on a significant corner allotment of 680m2 (approx), its era character is displayed through high decorative ceilings, OFPs & timber floors. With garden aspects from every window, its light-filled interior opens to traditional lounge & dining rooms, that transition to a modern stone kitchen with island bench & WIP & spacious family room with bay window. Outdoors, an entertaining deck with automatic blinds complements the private solar heated pool, whilst GDH, split system AC, poolhouse & single carport complete a gracious lifestyle sanctuary. Excellent scope & prospects on offer to an array of family, investor and developer buyers, move in & enjoy or capitalize on the versatile corner & consider new luxury townhouse options (STCA). Situated in the prized McKinnon Secondary College zone, moments to Joyce Park, train, shops & cafes.

Description:
Auction This Saturday at 11.00am
An Art Deco Classic Perfect for Family Living
Home is where the heart is, and your heart will fall for this cherished 4 bedroom 2 bathroom double fronted Art Deco home on a family size 691sqm approx. block.
Rich in period detail, it retains its original leadlight doors, windows & cabinets, warm timber detail, polished boards and high ornate ceilings. Primed for modern family living, this captivating home enjoys an enclosed porch, central hall, a gorgeous lounge, north facing dining room (OFP), 4 double bedrooms (3 with fitted BIRs), modern kitchen (Omega double oven & large pantry), a period style central bathroom, 2ndbathroom/laundry and a comfortable kids retreat or second living room.
Stay warm in winter with hydronic heating throughout, and cool in summer with evaporative cooling. Enjoy your weekends in the generous west-facing rear garden (with room to install a swimming pool), including a cheery cubby house, paved entertaining area and a shed and tandem carport for your outdoor storage
With loads of promise to extend if desired or update as you please, this heartwarming home is in this quiet street, close to cafes, the Elsternwick/Chadstone bus, Packer Park, McKinnon Primary School and other leading schools, and a short walk to Ormond station, shops and restaurants.

Description:
Perfectly positioned, beautifully presented, in-Zone
Wonderfully situated in the heart of the McKinnon Secondary College zone, only a stroll from North Road's train station, buses, shops and restaurants, this single-level three-bedroom two-bathroom home offers spacious, open-plan living on a low-maintenance allotment. Beautifully presented throughout, it features abundant natural light and a private, sunny outdoor entertaining terrace.
Capturing northern sunshine it comprises a large, sun-drenched open-plan living and dining room that's adjacent to a gourmet kitchen featuring granite benchtops, European appliances and tiled splashbacks, three bedrooms (all with built-in robes), main with a floor-to-ceiling tiled ensuite and walk-in-robe, a central bathroom that's also tiled from floor to ceiling, laundry with external access. Highlights include central heating, Bose sound system, reverse-cycle heat/cool units in the living room and main bedroom, security entry and window shutters, a very private entertaining courtyard that enjoys north and east facing sunshine, auto lock-up double garage with internal entry and electronically controlled gates.
Close to two shopping centres, public and private schools, Ormond and McKinnon train stations, the location ticks all the boxes.

Description:
Streetfront, Single-Level, Zone-Addressed
Front up to the McKinnon College Zone with fresh flair, great space and a prized streetfront position. A substantial single-level townhouse with classic street presence, this period-inspired home goes above and beyond with house-like three bedroom, two bathroom accommodation, private garden space front and rear, and a extensive array of extras.
Step inside beyond the iron-faced front garden and find a generous dual zone floorplan that places a large formal zone to the front, a private master-suite to the rear and a casual or dining area beside the quality appliance and stone benchtop kitchen. Beyond a gorgeous leadlight entry, red iron bark timber floors permeate the spacious interior, starring Miele appliances for the caesar stone kitchen, informal lounge and dining and a separate sitting room to compliment the family wise floorplan. Description:
875sqm Approx GRZ1 under $2000psqm!
On 875sqm approx. in the General Residential Zone 1, with the opportunity for a multi-dwelling development of either apartments or townhouses (STCA), this candid 4 bedroom 2 bathroom 1970s brick home is alive with options.
A sizeable single level home, this neatly maintained classic features a generous lounge & dining room, huge meals area, vintage kitchen, 4 bedrooms (BIRs, main with ensuite), a family bathroom, laundry and a double garage.
Easy to live in or let out while creating your vision, this eye-opening proposition is comfy cosy with polished boards, gas heating and a west-facing back yard that goes forever.
Well positioned for families, students and city professionals, minutes to Ormond station, North Road shops, Glen Huntly Village, Monash Uni Caulfield and Clayton campuses, parks, an outdoor pool, schools, childcare and the city tram. Currently leased on a month to month basis for $2167pcm.
SITE INSPECTIONS ONLY DURING MID WEEK INSPECTIONS. Interior of property can be inspected during weekend open homes.

Description:
Comfy Cosy in Ormond's Heart
An enormous surprise (95.7sqm approx) of easy care living, this tranquil 2 bedroom ground floor apartment is in this lifestyle pocket yet provides a quiet escape for those who love to live on the edge.
Enjoying leafy aspects, this well maintained abode features an entry hall, a glass door to an inviting living room with balcony, tastefully updated kitchen with large meals area (gas stove, loads of storage); 2 big bedrooms (BIRs), separate toilet and a classic bathroom with laundry facilities and a separate bath.
Perfect to live in or let out with its warm welcoming space, it boasts panel heating, an air conditioner, great storage, external blinds, security door, new window furnishings (double blinds) and a carport with body corporate already planning with current funds to refurbish the communal entry, carports and windows.
Opposite the Katandra School, and just a heartbeat to Kilvington Grammar, Ormond station, shops, cafes, restaurants, and Ormond's dynamic night life, just moments to the Monash Uni bus, parks and gardens.

Description:
Zone-in on Size, Space & Single Level Seclusion
Find peace and solitude in a prized McKinnon zone cul de Sac. Set peacefully at the rear of a long gated driveway, this red brick residence sets the pace for lifestyle ease with a choice of maintenance free outdoor zones front and back, an expansive bay windowed living room in-between and a quality tiled kitchen and meals area with Blanco appliances, ample bench and cupboard space.
Sleekly styled through 3 robed bedrooms with a stylish ensuite for the master (WIR), a main family bathroom and a laundry with courtyard access, this stunning family home enjoys the comforts of ducted heating, split system air con and a large single lock up garage with both internal and external access.
Move in and enjoy single level seclusion or take this solid home to a new level with a designer makeover or alternatively invest in a prestigious McKinnon Zone address - located moments to Joyce park & North Roads cosmopolitan precinct, minutes to Ormond train station and the back gates of the College and a short drive to GESAC. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.
